<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>The <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_hand">Hand</link> class reports the physical characteristics of a detected hand. </para>



<para><link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_hand">Hand</link> tracking data includes a palm position and velocity; vectors for the palm normal and direction to the fingers; and lists of the attached fingers.</para>

<para>Note that <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_hand">Hand</link> objects can be invalid, which means that they do not contain valid tracking data and do not correspond to a physical entity. Invalid <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_hand">Hand</link> objects can be the result of using the default constructor, or modifying the hand data in an incorrect way. <formalpara><title>Since: </title>

<para>1.0 </para>
</formalpara>
</para>
